126
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:21,810
The body of one of the soldiers patrolling East City Station has been found.

127
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:24,820
Blown up from the inside?

128
00:06:35,450 --> 00:06:37,050
Doctor Marcoh?

129
00:06:37,050 --> 00:06:38,980
You mean Mauro-sensei?

130
00:06:38,980 --> 00:06:40,600
No, <i>Marcoh</i>.

131
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:44,550
But there's only one doctor in this village, 
and that's Mauro-sensei.

132
00:06:44,550 --> 00:06:47,920
As you can see, the folks along this road are poor,

133
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:53,230
and we had to take half a day 
just to get to East City to see a doctor.

134
00:06:53,230 --> 00:06:54,740
He's a nice fellow.

135
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:59,270
He'll make sure to see even patients who were given up on as incurable elsewhere.

136
00:06:59,270 --> 00:07:02,860
When I got my leg caught under a tractor and it looked like I was going to die,

137
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:04,960
he fixed me up just right.

138
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,850
When he was treating him, right? There was this flash of light!

139
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:09,160
Right, right!

140
00:07:13,110 --> 00:07:14,780
Light...

141
00:07:14,780 --> 00:07:17,190
That's alchemy all right.

142
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:18,790
It's Doctor Marcoh.

143
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:21,460
But he's on the run 
from the military, right?

144
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:24,930
Why would he become a doctor? There'd be stories about him.

145
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:32,300
This is awful! 
I'm getting straw inside me!

146
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:37,750
Who is that?

147
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:39,480
He's a State Alchemist—

148
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:42,690
one of those who was with the Führer when they came from Central.

149
00:07:42,690 --> 00:07:44,580
But why is he here?

150
00:07:44,580 --> 00:07:46,650
Did he follow us?

151
00:07:46,650 --> 00:07:51,480
The Colonel said he never reported Marcoh's whereabouts to Central.

152
00:07:57,350 --> 00:08:00,670
Let's hurry! Marcoh's house should be close by.

153
00:08:09,260 --> 00:08:11,730
H-Hold on! We just wanted...

154
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:15,840
A State Alchemist, you say?! 
Have you come to take me back?!

155
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:19,850
Er, you're the Crystal Alchemist, Doctor Marcoh-san, right?

156
00:08:19,850 --> 00:08:23,770
I don't want to go back there! Please! I couldn't stand that!

157
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:25,600
It's not like that! Hear us out!

158
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,770
Look, that's dangerous!

159
00:08:27,770 --> 00:08:29,980
Or have you come to silence me?!

160
00:08:30,380 --> 00:08:33,930
You think you can kill me? I... I...

161
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:36,490
Al...

162
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,910
It's all right.

163
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:43,750
Even if you kill me, I won't die.

164
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:57,500
You're...

165
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,680
I see, you're the Fullmetal Alchemist...

166
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:07,730
No, that would be me! 
I'm him, actually.

167
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:20,030
I deserted the battlefield,

168
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:24,540
and when I did, I stole the research materials that I had at the time.

169
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:28,250
The military is probably 
still after those materials.

170
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,000
That's it!

171
00:09:31,210 --> 00:09:34,020
The truth is, we're looking into human transmutation—

172
00:09:34,020 --> 00:09:35,420
I can't...

173
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:37,930
show you anything.

174
00:09:38,690 --> 00:09:43,320
Orders from above notwithstanding, 
I stained my hands with that research.

175
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:47,940
And then, it was used in the 
massacre of the Eastern Rebellion.

176
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:50,660
Massacre?

177
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:52,690
You mean the uprising at Ishbal?

178
00:09:52,690 --> 00:09:54,520
It was terrible.

179
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:57,250
It was a truly terrible battle.

180
00:09:57,910 --> 00:10:00,120
Children... women...

181
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,120
They were all killed.

182
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:04,620
There was no justifiable reason for it.

183
00:10:04,620 --> 00:10:08,620
It was reason enough that they were the people of Ishbal and defied the military.

184
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:14,380
I could never fully make up for what 
I did there even if I gave up my own life.

185
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:20,270
Even so, I decided to do all that I can, which is why I am a doctor here.

186
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:24,630
Go back.

187
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:29,380
I'm a State Alchemist! 
I have a right to see your research!

188
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:31,610
As little as you are?

189
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:34,460
I'll bet you were blinded by 
the abundant research funding

190
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:37,310
and numerous privileges, 
so you got yourself certified.

191
00:10:37,310 --> 00:10:39,110
What foolishness.

192
00:10:39,660 --> 00:10:41,880
If you were there during 
the rebellion, you would also—

193
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:43,700
I know!

194
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:47,250
I know what we're doing is stupid. But even so...

195
00:10:51,380 --> 00:10:52,460
Marcoh-san...

196
00:10:53,180 --> 00:10:57,970
About five years ago, you treated 
the babies at Xenotime, didn't you?

197
00:10:58,290 --> 00:11:01,110
The babies from that time are now doing fine.

198
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:08,580
Brother!

199
00:11:12,350 --> 00:11:14,030
No transmutation circle?!

200
00:11:15,970 --> 00:11:20,280
Is this the red water of Xenotime? 
No, this appears to be much clearer.

201
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:22,210
Stop!

202
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,210
Brother!

203
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:24,990
Brother, this is wrong!

204
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,280
Let go of me!

205
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,240
Brother!

206
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:29,660
Let go of me, I said!

207
00:11:35,620 --> 00:11:36,950
It's not a liquid?

208
00:11:36,950 --> 00:11:38,420
Brother, it...

209
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:41,780
It looks like that thing that the Minister at Liore had.

210
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:49,020
The Sage's Stone, the Celestial Stone...

211
00:11:49,650 --> 00:11:53,730
the Great Elixir, the Red Tincture, the Fifth Element...

212
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,890
Just as it is called by many names,

213
00:11:56,890 --> 00:11:59,740
its form is also not limited to that of a stone.

214
00:11:59,740 --> 00:12:01,860
Brigadier General Grand...

215
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:03,650
Brigadier General?

216
00:12:03,650 --> 00:12:06,580
My, you've moved up in the world.

217
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:11,020
Crystal Alchemist,

218
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:14,630
you will turn over the Philosopher's Stone, along with all of your materials.

219
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:17,090
Philosopher's Stone?! That?!

220
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:21,430
At best, it is an experimentally produced item.

221
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:24,720
There's no telling when it will 
reach its limit and become unusable.

222
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:29,120
It's an unstable, defective product, 
and it's different from the genuine article.

223
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:32,990
But during the rebellion, 
it did augment our abilities,

224
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:35,710
and we displayed tremendous power!

225
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:51,800
So, are you saying 
that in the past,

226
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:54,460
the military researched 
the Philosopher's Stone?

227
00:12:54,460 --> 00:12:58,990
Never mind that it isn't perfect. 
If that was made by human hands...

228
00:12:58,990 --> 00:13:02,640
