Crystal Alchemist, Doctor Marcoh...

256
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:15,050
I heard that you were dead.

257
00:15:16,010 --> 00:15:19,020
I must take special care...

258
00:15:19,020 --> 00:15:21,020
to kill you!

259
00:15:21,650 --> 00:15:22,700
You're...

260
00:15:23,580 --> 00:15:26,730
I see. This must be fate.

261
00:15:27,410 --> 00:15:31,200
In the name of God, 
thou shalt perish!

262
00:15:35,370 --> 00:15:36,720
Edward-kun!

263
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:39,250
What are you giving up for?! Run!

264
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:41,800
Fullmetal Alchemist!

265
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:43,330
You will not escape either!

266
00:15:43,330 --> 00:15:47,090
<i>He knows me? 
What's going on here?</i>

267
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:50,880
<i>I've done plenty of stuff 
to get people mad at me,</i>

268
00:15:51,140 --> 00:15:53,220
<i>but I've never given anyone 
a reason to come after my life!</i>

269
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,220
Brother, this way!

270
00:16:36,090 --> 00:16:38,000
Who are you?!

271
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,640
Why are you after us?!

272
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:43,980
If you are creators, then there must also be a destroyer.

273
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:47,380
Edward-kun, leave me behind and run!

274
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,700
You have a fine look in your eyes.

275
00:16:57,700 --> 00:17:00,580
My older brother also had the same look in his eyes.

276
00:17:01,430 --> 00:17:07,730
Eyes that were strong, that peered far away 
into the endless distance...

277
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:13,130
Three years ago, was it?

278
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:17,800
I was glad to hear that you had 
given up being a State Alchemist.

279
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:21,180
That's too bad. However!

280
00:17:23,890 --> 00:17:24,690
Too slow!

281
00:17:26,190 --> 00:17:27,270
Brother!

282
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:37,200
Al!

283
00:17:37,780 --> 00:17:39,640
Make no mistake.

284
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:44,610
I meant to destroy a human body, 
so you got away with just that crack.

285
00:17:44,610 --> 00:17:46,210
Stay out of this.

286
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:49,580
My only enemy is the State Alchemist.

287
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:52,500
Why?

288
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,210
Why are you after us?

289
00:17:54,210 --> 00:17:57,440
Alchemists are those who take things 
from their natural form

290
00:17:57,440 --> 00:18:00,400
and transform them into something grotesque.

291
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:05,130
That is to say, they profane God, the creator of all things.

292
00:18:05,730 --> 00:18:09,040
As an agent of God,

293
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:11,440
I am he who hands down his judgment.

294
00:18:14,380 --> 00:18:18,140
I'm an alchemist too! 
I may not have the state's certification...

295
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:20,200
Why do you wish to die?

296
00:18:21,710 --> 00:18:24,480
You mentioned your older brother a moment ago, right?

297
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:26,410
Then you should understand!

298
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:30,090
There's no way anyone could watch their brother get killed.

299
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,920
Even you—

300
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:32,920
I do understand!

301
00:18:33,450 --> 00:18:38,730
The way I felt when I had to watch as 
my brother was killed before my eyes...

302
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:41,140
That is exactly...

303
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,930
why I must now...!

304
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:48,890
I told you, you're too slow.

305
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:00,830
Automail?

306
00:19:01,410 --> 00:19:04,620
So your right arm brings forth 
nothing but destruction as well?

307
00:19:04,620 --> 00:19:08,880
Don't go lumping my 
right arm in with yours!

308
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,970
A State Alchemist?

309
00:19:27,630 --> 00:19:29,530
Are you here to take Marcoh-san?!

310
00:19:36,890 --> 00:19:41,520
I'm sorry I'm late. I was assigned by the Lt. Colonel to guard you.

311
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:43,250
By Lt. Colonel Hughes?

312
00:19:45,020 --> 00:19:50,560
Agent of God, you say? In that case, try passing judgment upon me.

313
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:53,190
For I am the Strong Arm Alchemist,

314
00:19:53,830 --> 00:19:56,710
Alex Louis Armstrong!

315
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:01,500
What a fine day this is!

316
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:04,970
That you would come forward 
and save me the trouble of finding you...

317
00:20:05,730 --> 00:20:07,680
Could this be the grace of God?

318
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:09,400
Allow me to show you 
the artistic alchemy

319
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:14,860
that has been passed down among 
the Armstrong family for generations!

320
00:20:19,650 --> 00:20:21,490
Another shot!

321
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:30,600
As you can see, 
there are only children here!

322
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,040
There aren't any of the guerillas you're looking for!

323
00:20:35,660 --> 00:20:39,420
Does this mean you've abandoned 
the so-called teachings of Cornello?

324
00:20:39,420 --> 00:20:40,850
Fine.

325
00:20:40,850 --> 00:20:44,620
Tell us the location of the faction that's resisting military rule!

326
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:45,550
No!

327
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:53,060
We came to liberate this town from Cornello! 
Don't you understand?!

328
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:57,050
This town is our home.

329
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,660
We're going to move forward,

330
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:02,050
even if it's only a little at a time, under our own power.

331
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:05,780
Our legs are fine, after all!

332
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,090
You dropped this.

333
00:21:26,620 --> 00:21:31,120
You didn't think about 
running away with this?

334
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:35,100
You used it to treat people in that clinic, right?

335
00:21:36,260 --> 00:21:41,610
I can't forget the looks on the faces of 
those people who told us about you today.

336
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:49,410
That belongs to those people, and so do you.

337
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:52,870
Can you walk?

338
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:55,810
Okay, let's go.

339
00:21:55,810 --> 00:21:59,130
Someplace where neither that guy nor the military will follow us.

340
00:21:59,980 --> 00:22:01,750
Can we escape them?

341
00:22:03,310 --> 00:22:06,090
You still have your legs, don't you?

342
00:22:21,980 --> 00:22:26,850
You squeeze your right hand, as if to reassure yourself

343
00:22:21,980 --> 00:22:26,850
tashikameru you ni nigirishimeta migite

344
00:22:26,850 --> 00:22:31,700
Go on, take those annoying rules and dash them away!

345
00:22:26,850 --> 00:22:31,700
uzattai housoku o buchikowashite yuke

346
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:36,840
If it comes down to having to rest your wounded feet,

347
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:36,840
kizutsuita ashi o yasumaseru gurai nara

348
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:41,730
you've gotta keep moving forward, if only just a step!

349
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:41,730
tatta ippo demo koko kara susume

350
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:46,500
We've pushed our way

351
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:46,500
through the twisting winds

352
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:46,500
yuganda kaze o kaki wakete

353
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:51,630
and gotten beyond the cold sky

354
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:51,630
tsumetai sora o oikoshite

355
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:58,400
Yet we still continue to wander

356
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:58,400
soredemo mada samayoi tsuzuketeru

357
00:23:01,940 --> 00:23:06,570
We always find ourselves crying out

358
00:23:01,940 --> 00:23:06,570
bokura wa itsudemo sakenderu

359
00:23:06,570 --> 00:23:11,910
Just continuing to believe is not the answer

360
00:23:06,570 --> 00:23:11,910
shinji tsuzukeru dake ga kotae janai

361
00:23:11,910 --> 00:23:16,620
We must bare our weaknesses and wounds,

362
00:23:11,910 --> 00:23:16,620
yowasa mo kizu mo sarake dashite

363
00:23:16,620 --> 00:23:21,300
and continue to struggle,

364
00:23:16,620 --> 00:23:21,300
or nothing will ever turn out!

365
00:23:16,620 --> 00:23:21,300
mogaki tsuzukenakereba hajimaranai

366
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:29,000
Break on through to the other side of the door!

367
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:29,000
tsukiyabure tobira no mukou e

368
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:34,600
To the other side of the door!

369
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:34,600
tobira no mukou e

370
00:23:38,620 --> 00:23:40,220
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist</i>...

371
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:41,000
The Ishbal Massacre

372
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:40,950
The Ishbal Massacre

373
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:43,020
The Ishbal Massacre

374
00:23:40,220 --> 00:23:43,020
Episode 15: "The Ishbal Massacre"

375
00:23:44,770 --> 00:23:46,940
We don't know anything.

376
00:23:47,610 --> 00:23:51,150
But you can't use ignorance as an excuse to absolve yourself.

